Former Nelson Mandela Bay mayor Nceba Faku has withdrawn from the ANC Eastern Cape leadership race and is instead lobbying for former deputy finance minister Mcebisi Jonas for the top provincial post.If Jonas enters the race he will be going up against provincial secretary Oscar Mabuyane and premier Phumulo Masualle who is fighting to retain the ANC chairmanship.Despite the fact that the two slates have been up and running for several months Jonas s backers are optimistic that the branches will support him.Faku forms part of an ANC lobby group Save the Revolution which has been taking Jonas s name to the branches.Faku said he had decided to back Jonas after assessing the progress of his campaign. Full story in The Herald 